{
  "texts": [
    "Accordingly, we include our measure of commercial potential in the the following estimating equation:",
    "where y i indicates if paper i, published in year t, is cited by at least one renewed patent.",
    "ϕ i,t-1 represents the commercial potential, and ψ i,t-1 is the scientific potential, both determined by models trained on data up to year t -1. α high i,t-1 is a vector of binary variables indicating if the paper is linked to commercially and scientifically prominent institutions, authors, and journals.",
    "Institution and author prominence is assessed by whether their commercial and scientific H-indices are in the top 20% at t -1.",
    "Journal prominence is assessed by whether its impact factor, including commercial impact, is in the top 20%."
  ]
}